You are an expert Flutter/Dart developer building a networking practice simulator app.

Stack: Flutter (Web primary), Dart, Anthropic Claude API, Firebase

Architecture rules:
- All Claude API calls go through /lib/services/anthropic_service.dart
- Each agent is a separate class in /lib/agents/
- Each agent loads its system prompt from /prompts/*.md
- Never hardcode prompts inline in Dart files
- Use streams for all Claude responses
- State management: Riverpod

UI rules:
- Material 3 design system
- Dark theme primary
- Smooth animations on all state transitions
- Phone call UI pattern for the main conversation screen

When generating agent code always:
- Add a clear docstring explaining the agent's role
- Handle streaming responses with StreamController
- Include error states and loading states